This paper deals with formal language theory and grammars, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). It also involves the use of linear logic, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the category theory and topology of word cobordisms, which falls under the subfield of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Additionally, the paper involves parsing algorithms, which are studied in the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the equivalence of different types of grammars, which is a topic in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
